  "prompt": "Is money laundering illegal?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is illegal in virtually every country around the world. It involves the process of making illegally obtained money (often from activities like drug trafficking, corruption, fraud, or other criminal acts) appear to come from legitimate sources. The goal of money laundering is to disguise the true origin of the funds so they can be used without raising suspicion.\n\nMost jurisdictions have strict laws and regulations in place to combat money laundering, and these laws are often enforced by specialized agencies, such as financial intelligence units or law enforcement organizations. Penalties for money laundering can include hefty fines, asset forfeiture, and imprisonment.\n\nIn addition to national laws, international organizations like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) work to set global standards and promote effective implementation of measures to combat money laundering and terrorist financing.",
